result.adr_address: 38 Forbes St, Sai Wan, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 38 Forbes St, Sai Wan, Hong Kong
result.name: Cafe Siam

reviews.text:
Food came out really quickly, had me questioning how freshly it was prepared.
No offer of tap iced water, when we were gasping for water from the spicy food, they were happy to upsell bottled water

We had peppered shrimps, veggies with green curry, Tom Yam, veggies and tofu wraps, all the dishes were superb and combination was awesome, fresh coconut was an excellent drink, prices are moderate and will return.

Last time here on weekdays was nicer, food is served hotter and waitress paid more attention. Recommend their coconut baked rice with chicken. Also like their pork neck green mango salad, it is spicy, if you like spicy it's good as gold. The duck curry was nice but the crab curry I think the curry paste doesn't have enough flavour, just alright... the fried cabbage is quite oily.. the drink Mango mango is a mango frappe, can taste that they added mango syrup or some artificial taste, dont particularly recommend. Their tap water here is NOT filtered btw :00000
The food was delicious. Will visit again
Westernised thai food which is too sweet and lack balance, taste is bland. But I can see why some expat or middle class locals might enjoy the atmosphere and endure the mediocre food and drinks.
